    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="798"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d798">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867.24/286: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Welles</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Assistant Secretary of State</hi>
                        (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Acheson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-13">March 13,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Acheson</hi>: A copy of telegram 144, March 11, 4 p.m.
                    from Ankara has been sent to you. I fully share Mr. Steinhardt’s views and in
                    accordance with the policy we have all agreed upon, prompt action should now be
                    taken to give some concrete evidence to the Turkish Government that we are doing
                    something for it.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
